  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "ETIENNE CHARLOTTE TALPERT",
    "text": "I am Etienne, Joseph's wife for almost 45 years. My message to the future generations of our people is always remember who you are and where you come from. The most important feature is your identity. Never deny your roots. We are a people of pride. Family unity to be upheld and maintained. What is born to you is yours forever. I would like to end with a little quotation from an old movie to my beloved Joseph. 'The life that I have is all that I have. And the life that I have is yours. The love that I have for the life that I have is yours and yours and yours.' I love you, Joseph.",
    "start_ms": 231292,
